check 75: default_type_mismatch.

{"type": "integer", "default": "5"}

that's a string default for an integer param. the model might pass "5" or ignore the default. either way, wrong.

the most common version:

{"type": "boolean", "default": "false"}

copy-pasted from prose. OpenAPI auto-gen loves doing this. "false" (string) and false (boolean) are different things.
